en coty added coty “” indelible lipstick to its range in  using the theme ‘wake up beautiful with “alive” color glowing on your lips’ it proved to be a big seller and affected revlon’s sales even further between hazel bishop and coty revlon’s share of the american lipstick market hit an all time low abrams  p  in  to combat hazel bishop revlon added indeliblecreme lipstick to its regular lipstick but was forced to abandoned it in  when the us federal trade commission ftc got agreement from advertisers that lipsticks can only claim to be ‘indelible’ ‘smearproof’ or ‘nonsmear’ if the word ‘type’ was used with such descriptions its replacement was lanolite lipstick a greasy lanolin enriched lipstick in nonsmear and regular formulations but sales were disappointing in  in response to coty “” revlon introduced living lipstick the twentyfour hour type with the line ‘put living color on your lips’ an obvious copy of coty’s ‘alive’ rather than face a protracted legal battle with revlon for copying coty simply informed international playtex – who had a trademark on ‘living’ for living bras that included toiletries – and revlon was forced to also cease production of this line under threat of a court action revlon’s lustrous lipstick – the fourth lipstick revlon had marketed since  – went on sale in  one year after revlon released the futurama refillable lipstick cases designed by the jewellers van cleef  arpels when futurama was first put on the market women could chose to insert either living lanolite or regular lipsticks  and then later lanolite lustrous or living lipsticks  this was too much the choice confused women and revlon got trade complaints about the need to stock three different types of lipstick in a wide range of colours and refills living lipstick was dropped because of the playtex legal suit and revlon dumped over  lanolite lipsticks off its inventory abrams  p  leaving only lustrous lipstick remaining above  revlon living lustrous and lanolite lipsticks fortunately for revlon it was now in a position to bear the cost of this by  it was the sole advertiser of the hottest television show in the america ‘the  question’ with it revlon won the lipstick wars and coty and hazel bishop were no longer considered a major threat ‘the  question’ revlon had previously sponsored a number of television shows including ‘revlon mirror theater’ ‘mr and mrs north’ ‘what’s going on’ and ‘whom do you trust’ none of which had proved to be successful in its battle with hazel bishop and their television program ‘this is your life’ revson had little choice but to try again and much against his better judgement he agreed to be come the sole sponsor of yet another television program ‘the  question’ the show first went to air on th june  and after a slow start proved to be a phenomenon almost anything revlon advertised on it got a massive sales boost the company’s sales jumped from us to us in  – even though the program had only been televised for six months – and had more than doubled to us by  the year the show went off the air abrams  p  see also revlon and ‘the  question’ by  revlon was the number one seller of lipstick hairspray nail products and makeup tobias  p  and way out in front of all of its competitors even outselling avon revlon had also gone public on december   six months after the debut of ‘the  question’ the shares began at us but hit us within a few weeks and were split twoforone in  helena rubinstein may have been a rival but even she had revlon shares however charles revson was soon on his own joseph revson left the firm in  and martin followed in  in both cases the departures were acrimonious other lines while engaged in the lipstick wars revlon was expanding its product range in a number of directions the company added to its makeup range with second nature  a liquid makeup base lovepat  a pressed powdercream and touch  glow face powder  it also developed a skincare range beginning with white sable liquid cleansing cream  followed by moon drops  a moisturising balm clean and clear  a foaming cleanser containing hexachlorophene build up  a firming facial waking beauty  a night cream containing vitamins a d and e liquid asset  a skin normaliser and ultima  a face cream above  some of revlon’s products produced in the year it became a public company and listed on the stock exchange included are lipsticks futurama lipstick cases nail enamels hair sprays touch and glow liquid makeup and face powder lovepat and fashion plate compacts aquamarine products buildup firming facial moon drops moisture balm waking beauty enriched night creme white sable cleansing creme and second nature estrogenic liquid makeup eyeshadow eyebrow pencil and mascara silicare clean and clear deep cleansing liquid cheekstick liquid and cake rouge manicuring equipment and assorted fragrances revson also began to show a greater interest in perfumes if he had not been previously convinced about the importance of fragrance the success of estée lauder’s youth dew bath oil  must have certainly attracted his attention in  making one of his infrequent public appearances as a speech maker he told the national association of chain store druggists “get a fragrance going and you’ve got everything soaps powders afterbath colognes bath beads — you name it” revson saw the line extension possibilities of fragrances as a money machine which could keep turning out product after product once the public accepted the basic essence he also believed fragrances were one of the few untouchable areas free of government fda and ftc regulation “y’know what they’d have to put on a fragrance label” he told me once “hopes and dreams — not ingredients kiddie — hopes and dreams” abrams  p  revson had already followed this idea by releasing the aquamarine line scent being made available as a spray mist in  the same year that he released fire and ice parfum in  revlon introduced intimate a perfume that imitated dior’s miss dior first sold back in  with some reluctance revson agreed to it being advertised on television – the first fragrance to be promoted this way – and within a year it was one of the six largest selling fragrances in the world again helped along by ‘the  question’ other products produced by revlon in the s included silicare  a hand protectant silicare medicated hand and body lotion  sun bath  a beauty tanning lotion top brass  a men’s hair dressing hi and dri  a roll on deodorant the antibiotic neomycin added in  living curl  a hair spray and thin down  tablets for weight reduction containing an appetite depressant and vitamins some of these came from revlon’s increasing interest in pharmaceuticals the company had been acquiring pharmaceutical firms and adding them to its pharmaceutical division instituted in  some of its pharmaceutical products were related to skincare but others like femicin a medication for period pain were drugs pure and simple prestige cosmetics by  – thanks largely to the success of ‘the  question’ – revlon had become one of the biggest cosmetic firms in the united states only avon had larger overall sales rather than being happy about this charles revson was worried revson knew that there was a difference between a commodity and a fashion item a commodity is used until it is finished and competitors usually compete on price a fashion item can be discarded long before the product is used up and competitors differentiate themselves through creativity and marketing skill with a product that is priced accordingly as they were primarily about colour revson could market nail enamels and lipsticks as fashion items with new colours appearing each spring and autumn they were advertised extensively and marketed through packaging displays and promotional tieins with fashion magazines and department stores which allowed revlon to set a premium price the publishers information bureau indicated that revlon spent us on magazine advertising in  a single advertisement in the new yorker us in  us in  after lipstick was added to the inventory and us in  apeor  revlon advertised heavily in relation to its sales – and in its early days borrowed heavily to fund it – which gave people the impression that the company was a lot bigger than it really was tobias  p  it also helped establish revlon as a producer of prestigious products in the minds of its customers a key to this strategy was maintaining a degree of exclusivity to preserve its prestigious image as a high fashion high margin brand revlon had to control distribution and keep its products out of stores that would cheapen the brand and lead to price competition for the most part revlon had managed to do this restricting its products to ‘selected’ stores and salons revlon entered the s as a relatively luxurious nail polish and lipstick brand but it ended the decade largely as a mass marketer this was mainly due to the success of its television advertising but it was also partly the result of the inclusion of new products that were more difficult to promote as fashion items revson was very aware of this problem and battled to try and maintain revlon or at least parts of the company as a highend brand the tv campaign had tripled revlon sales but it had also made it more mass than class just the opposite of what charles revson had planned he urged me to retain at least the combination of mass and class and we had been able to do that through a combination of restricted distribution luxury packaging and higher than average pricing still there was no denying that the one thing revlon was losing in the process of growth was “class” abrams  p  abrams suggests that there was more to revson’s obsession with class than simple economics revson argued that the quality image of his top lines would enhance the image of basic revlon but pride not profit was his fundamental motivation in taking the course he did abrams  p  revson’s concern about prestige was the main reason behind a number of developments including the princess marcella borghese line  – the first time revlon had used a ‘celebrity’ endorsement – the opening of ‘the house of revlon’ beauty salon in new york  and the introduction of the ultima ii line  princess marcella borghese after negotiations with princess marcella borghese  in italy princess marcella borghese inc was registered as an american corporation in  after which the princess travelled to the united states to help develop the line things did not go smoothly expected personal formulas for cosmetics proved to be nonexistent abrams  p  and after the line was released in  fabergé took revlon to court charging that the borghese packaging and promotion copied their julliette marglen line these problems may have turned revson against it and be part of the reason why princess marcella borghese was not mentioned in company reports until  diversification other issues for charles revson were the fickle nature of the cosmetic business and potential limitations on the growth of the company both issues made more pressing by the fact that revlon had become a public company in  and these factors affected its share price above  new factory space acquired by revlon from johnson  johnson in edison new jersey to help cope with the increased demand it was located near the main line of the pennsylvania railway the company occupied the site in july  starting in  with knomark inc the makers of esquire shoe polish revlon began acquiring a number of businesses that charles revson hoped would maintain growth and reduce the company’s dependance on cosmetics purchases were relatively modest in the s but picked up considerably in the next decade timeline brothers charles and joseph revson and charles r lachman establish revlon revlon nail enamel corporation established new products adheron a basecoat revlon makes its first large sale to the marshall field department store martin revson joins revlon revlon’s first ad appears in ‘the new yorker’ magazine new products new cream polish remover that lubricates the nails as it removes the polish revlon opens a store account with saks fifth avenue new showroom opens at  west th street new york revlon style department opens revlon export corporation organised new products solvent a nail polish thinner prolon a cream designed to prevent nails from splitting and breaking and lactol a brittle nail treatment revlon nail enamel corporation changes its name to revlon products corporation revlon introduces lipsticks to match its nail enamels  new products pearl hand cream and cheek stick a cream rouge in a stick form  new products sealfast a clear topcoat and revlon lipstick brush  revlon reorganises its shade range new products windmilled face powders and leg silk leg makeup revlon begins fullcolor photographic advertisements revlon acquires graef  schmidt inc new york to manufacturing its own manicure equipment chicago office at  east washington square opened new products everon base coat and lucite lipstick cases revlon enters the market in great britain new products aquamarine lotion and fashion plate a pressedcream makeup  new products lip fashion a slim lipstick  new products touch  glow a liquid makeup nailfix for mending broken nails and dreamy eye makeup new factories opened in england and france new products indeliblecreme lipstick match maker sets introduced to encourage matching of lipsticks and nail enamel new products white sable liquid cleansing cream and second nature a liquid makeup base  new products moon drops moisture balm for dry skin cuticle massage cream and creamy cuticle remover added to the nail builder line lovepat a pressed powdercream makeup waking beauty night cream treatment for dry skin and silicare a hand protectant  new products fire and ice parfum lanolite lipstick in nonsmear and regular formulations buildup an astringent skin tightener silkennet a liquid hair spray and quickdry nonsmear nail spray revlon changes its name to revlon inc and goes public new manufacturing facilities acquired in edison new jersey revlon pharmaceutical division established joseph revson leaves revlon new products intimate parfum futurama lipstick cases living lipstick the twentyfour hour type lustrous lipstick superbase a base coat lastron nail enamel a combination of nylon and cellulose acetate touch  glow face powder clean and clear a liquid cleanser silicare medicated hand lotion and satinset hair spray thayer laboratories a drug division established new products medicated baby silicare lotion and sun bath sun tan lotion and aquamarine spray mist ideal toy company begins manufacture of revlon dolls sales department reorganised after the sales force had been doubled in  new products touch  glow pressed powder futurama compacts containing lovepat shades refillable waterproof cream mascara clean and clear for very dry skin liquid asset a twophase liquid to normalise both dry and oily skins seven wonders dry skin cream and hi and dri roll on deodorant martin revson leaves revlon revlon acquires a  stake in schick inc new products princess marcella borghese line moon drops moisture foundation thin down tablets for weight reduction wonder base a base coat living curl a hair spray rollon mascara revlon’s first automatic mascara intimate milk bath and intimate bubble bath and top brass deodorant and top brass after shave lotion bressard hair products corporation and bressard distributors inc makers of hair colours acquired revlon buys the distribution rights of revillion parfums of paris for the usa and canada revlon gains a controlling interest in les parfums pierre balmain of paris new products ultima a face cream intimate hand lotion intimate fragrance mist aquamarine after bath freshener aquamarine milk bath top brass cologne and colorup a cream hair conditioner and color rinse realistic company of cincinnati makers of professional beauty salon products bought revlon professional aimed at the professional salon industry established new products ultima makeup collection liquid foundations powders and lipsticks in natural complexion tints moon drops line established with the addition of moon drops moisturizing cleanser and moon drops facial freshener continued to revlon post updated rd april  sources abrams g j  that man the story of charles revson new york manor books inc broadcasting telecasting  washington dc broadcasting publications inc dallaire v j  from and idea to  the american perfumer  essential oil review february  nail enamel  drug and cosmetic industry   tedlow r s  giants of enterprise seven business innovators and the empires they built new york harpercollins publishers inc television magazine new york frederick kugel company inc tobias a  fire and ice the story of charles revson—the man who built the revlon empire new york william morrow revlon inc annual reports  rise of revlon  the american perfumer  essential oil review may  woodhead l  war paint miss elizabeth arden and madame helena rubinstein their lives their times their rivalry london virago charles haskell revson   revlon nail polish revlon’s first advertisement in ‘the new yorker’ august  was the new york socialite entirely fictional or was revson referring to diane vreeland who had returned to new york in may  revlon nail polish charles revson would later insist on using the word ‘enamel’ instead of ‘polish’ as he thought it sounded ‘classier’  revlon nail enamels in a bottle shape the company would use through to  revlon nail enamels now came in  shades including cubana a reddish brown riviera an ashes of roses tint ascot a rich glowing red with a bit of purple newport for suntanned skins nassau a glowing sunset red suez a dusky brownish red sierra a medium rose softened with brown and mauve lancer a blush rose for blue shades and tartar for greys blacks and neutral clothing  revlon hand sculpture manicure one of a range of manicures revlon suggested  revlon lipsticks colours included shy a wistful mauvetinged pink for shy shell and lancer nail enamels windsor for windsor and savoy nail enamels sun rose for sun rose riviera sudan and sierra nail enamels bravo a clear unabashed scarlet for bravo and amoa red nail enamels juelton jueltone  jueltone  and jueltone  nail enamels red dice a glorious red for red dice and ascot nail enamels chilibean an exotic brownseasoned rose for chilibean and suez nail enamels tringar a gyspsy rosered for tringar  tringar  and tringar  nail enamels and mahogany for the mahogany nail enamel  revlon quick trick  revlon cheek stick  revlon pearlglow nail enamel a pearlescent nail polish  new matching shades by revlon for fingertips lips and cheeks revlon’s cheek stick rouge was introduced in   revlon sealfast the sealcote co charged revlon with copying their sealcote product  revlon lipstick and nail enamel in mrs miniver rose shade “in the impersonal stillness of a motion picture theatre we in america have met mrs miniver and loved her completely and like the gentle old station master who grew the mrs miniver rose and said so staunchly ‘there’ll always be roses’ we of revlon know there’ll always be women like mrs miniver”  revlon nail polishes  revlon rosy future an almost perfect shade name for wartime  revlon windmilled face power nail enamel and lipstick in matching tournament of roses shade revlon introduced face powder into its range in   revlon cherry coke scarlet slipper and bravo shades note the slogan revlon used was ‘fingertips and lips’ not ‘lips and fingertips’ as is often incorrectly reported this makes sense as at this stage revlon was still mainly a nail enamel company  revlon dynamite face power nail enamel and lipstick beginning in  revlon began launching fullcolor photographic advertisements in major magazines and stores across the country  revlon pink lightning face powder  revlon cinderella’s pumpkin  revlon goldstick the lipstick case was a reproduction of a limited edition  karat gold case revlon had released the previous year the case would also be used in the revlon ultima line  revlon lip fashion  revlon’s orchids for you face power nail enamel and lipstick the nail enamel is packaged in a new bottle design and the lipstick is available in both regular and longer lip fashion forms  revlon fashion plate pressedcream makeup first introduced in  in  shades it was encased in a roseivory ‘plate’ rimmed with rubyred lucite  revlon touchandglow a liquid matt makeup in seven shades candles became so strongly associated with touchandglow that they usually appear in other advertisements for this product  revlon fire and ice one of the most successful print campaigns the company ran the dress had a front – covered in rhinestones mostly sewn on by a man who did costumes for strippers – but no back and was held in place with safety pins the scarlet cape was a copy of one by balenciaga that kay daley had seen in paris tobias  the lipstick was available in indeliblecreme and regular formulations with the regular and frosted nail enamels made to an ‘improved formulation’  revlon aquamarine lotion the lotion would be followed by a number of line extensions that made up the aquamarine range  revlon queen of diamonds shade revlon nail enamels in this time were referred to as wear longer nail enamels presumably in response to hazel bishop’s longlasting nail polish introduced in   revlon lovepat originally released in eight shades cream beige cream ivory dark rachel sun tan light light light misty rose and rachel  revlon moon drops moisture balm it was considered rather ‘bland’ and was not wildly successful woodhead  p  revlon added moon drops moisture foundation in  and later turned moon drops into a complete line  revlon silicare medicated hand and body lotion  revlon intimate parfum  revlon futurama lipstick cases these went on sale in  after revlon acquired the braselton lipstick patents for lipstick cartridges in  despite the fact that they were produced in response to similar cases developed by helena rubinstein revlon entered into an agreement with her and merle norman – along with a number of container manufacturers including scovill and risdon – to fix the price of lipstick refills including nonpatented lipstick inserts until they were charged by the us federal trade commission ftc with conspiracy apeor   futurama lipstick cases  revlon lustrous lipstick in futurama cases  princess marcella borghese although the cosmetics may have been ‘italian inspired’ the recipes came from revlon’s laboratory  femicin from thayer laboratories released in  this was the first product produced by revlon’s pharmaceutical division  revlon clean and clear  revlon top brass  revlon moon drops moisture balm and moisture foundation  princess marcella borghese velluto  revlon touchandglow makeup  revlon sun bath  revlon ultima   if you liked this share it   james bennett   email cosmeticsandskingmailcom twitter cosmeticsskin vogues in beauty come and go then crop up again in the neverceasing search for something new—g vail    ↑ top ultima ii cosmetics line  wikipedia ultima ii cosmetics line from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search ultima ii product type cosmetics skin care owner revlon inc country new york introduced  related brands revlon natural wonder charlie markets world website wwwultimaiicom ultima ii cosmetics line is a cosmetics and skin care line owned by revlon inc contents  history  growth  spokesmodels  external links  references historyedit the ultima name was originally coined by bea castle the highest placed female executive working for revlon at the time for a new moisturising cream  ultima the precious cream following on from the success of the moisturiser revlon founder charles revson created the charles revson inc company in  as the vehicle for his new top of the range line ultima ii revson claimed it was his favorite and most personal line and it was the only line to which he directly attached his name until the launch of revlons charlie perfume in  growthedit to promote the brand charles revsons private yacht was named ultima ii to keep with tradition present revlon owner ronald perelman named his yacht ultima iii ultima ii was always intended to be an upmarket cosmetic line as opposed to the core range revlon and youth range natural wonder in a marketing strategy called laddering inspired by general motors advertising targeted upperclass women and featured models clad in haute couture gowns for a decade ultima iis slogan was dedicated to the woman who spends a lifetime living up to her potential ultima iis launch and advertising techniques were likely a response to the growing success of competitor estée lauder who also aimed for an upmarket position in the cosmetic skin care and fragrance industry in  ultima ii became the first cosmetics company to sign a model lauren hutton  to an exclusive contract the move gained enough attention to make lauren the first fashion model to grace the cover of newsweek magazine ultima ii went one step further and signed photographer richard avedon as her exclusive photographer in  ultima ii partnered with jeweller aldo cipullo of cartier to sell an authorized reproduction of the love bracelet cartier which he had designed six years earlier in  ultima ii hired a yearold kevyn aucoin to produce a new line of makeup products  the new nakeds  making kevyn the youngest ever creative director for a major cosmetics company the new nakeds collection was notable because it was the first time a major cosmetics company launched a collection with shades that were suitable for all races of women and thus became highly popular in  revlon decided to expand distribution of ultima ii from prestige department stores into moderate ones like jc penney and drugstores like cvs taking on a more massmarket approach when revlon made the decision to withdraw all of its department store counters the brands success soon began to decline it was discontinued in north america in  in europe a market specific range was produced by epb leuropeenee des produits de beaute a revlon subsidiary in france it was withdrawn from sale in europe in  however ultima ii is available in asia specifically chinahong kong and indonesia having moderate success with their clear white and extraordinaire ranges there is now an ultima ii beauty institute in the sogo department store in hong kong the current range includes supreme caviar dna extraordinaire extraordinaire supreme procollagen extrema chr charles haskel revsons initials hydra botanic clear white supreme vital radiance once launched as a standalone brand in the us full moisture underitall  plus colour cosmetics including lipsticks  glosses mascaras foundations powders eye shadows  liners cheek blushers spokesmodelsedit lauren hutton modelled exclusively for ultima ii in the s and s she was the nations first cosmetics model to hold an exclusive contract models cybill shepherd aurélie claudel monique chevalier and jenny brunt also represented the brand actress titi kamal is the current famous face of ultima ii in indonesia external linksedit ultima iis official site ultima iis indonesian site referencesedit ultimaiicom  httpsnewsgooglecomnewspapersniddatidhjnwaaaaibajsjidpucdaaaaibajpg  fire and ice  httpwwwultimaiicomheritagemilestone v t e cosmetics face antiaging cream bb cream botulinum toxin botox concealer cleanser facial facial toning foundation moisturizer permanent makeup primer powder rouge skin whitening toner veil venetian ceruse lips lipstick gloss liner plumper stain balm eyes blepharoplasty circle contact lens eyelash extensions eyelid glue eye liner eye shadow kohl mascara hair conditioner hair coloring and bleaching removal chemical electric laser ipl plucking shaving threading waxing shampoo styling styling products gel mousse pomade spray wax nails artificial nails buffing manicure nail polish pedicure body body powder cold cream lotion cosmetic surgery peeling skin whitening related topics cosmetic electrotherapy cosmetic i