ltima ii cosmetics line is a cosmetics and skin care line owned by revlon inc contents  history  growth  spokesmodels  external links  references historyedit the ultima name was originally coined by bea castle the highest placed female executive working for revlon at the time for a new moisturising cream  ultima the precious cream following on from the success of the moisturiser revlon founder charles revson created the charles revson inc company in  as the vehicle for his new top of the range line ultima ii revson claimed it was his favorite and most personal line and it was the only line to which he directly attached his name until the launch of revlons charlie perfume in  growthedit to promote the brand charles revsons private yacht was named ultima ii to keep with tradition present revlon owner ronald perelman named his yacht ultima iii ultima ii was always intended to be an upmarket cosmetic line as opposed to the core range revlon and youth range natural wonder in a marketing strategy called laddering inspired by general motors advertising targeted upperclass women and featured models clad in haute couture gowns for a decade ultima iis slogan was dedicated to the woman who spends a lifetime living up to her potential ultima iis launch and advertising techniques were likely a response to the growing success of competitor estée lauder who also aimed for an upmarket position in the cosmetic skin care and fragrance industry in  ultima ii became the first cosmetics company to sign a model lauren hutton  to an exclusive contract the move gained enough attention to make lauren the first fashion model to grace the cover of newsweek magazine ultima ii went one step further and signed photographer richard avedon as her exclusive photographer in  ultima ii partnered with jeweller aldo cipullo of cartier to sell an authorized reproduction of the love bracelet cartier which he had designed six years earlier in  ultima ii hired a yearold kevyn aucoin to produce a new line of makeup products  the new nakeds  making kevyn the youngest ever creative director for a major cosmetics company the new nakeds collection was notable because it was the first time a major cosmetics company launched a collection with shades that were suitable for all races of women and thus became highly popular in  revlon decided to expand distribution of ultima ii from prestige department stores into moderate ones like jc penney and drugstores like cvs taking on a more massmarket approach when revlon made the decision to withdraw all of its department store counters the brands success soon began to decline it was discontinued in north america in  in europe a market specific range was produced by epb leuropeenee des produits de beaute a revlon subsidiary in france it was withdrawn from sale in europe in  however ultima ii is available in asia specifically chinahong kong and indonesia having moderate success with their clear white and extraordinaire ranges there is now an ultima ii beauty institute in the sogo department store in hong kong the current range includes supreme caviar dna extraordinaire extraordinaire supreme procollagen extrema chr charles haskel revsons initials hydra botanic clear white supreme vital radiance once launched as a standalone brand in the us full moisture underitall  plus colour cosmetics including lipsticks  glosses mascaras foundations powders eye shadows  liners cheek blushers spokesmodelsedit lauren hutton modelled exclusively for ultima ii in the s and s she was the nations first cosmetics model to hold an exclusive contract models cybill shepherd aurélie claudel monique chevalier and jenny brunt also represented the brand actress titi kamal is the current famous face of ultima ii in indonesia external linksedit ultima iis official site ultima iis indonesian site referencesedit ultimaiicom  httpsnewsgooglecomnewspapersniddatidhjnwaaaaibajsjidpucdaaaaibajpg  fire and ice  httpwwwultimaiicomheritagemilestone v t e cosmetics face anti